Elgar Peerschke was appointed president, Advisory Services in 2014. Bringing more than 25 years of experience to Quintiles, Elgar joined Quintiles from Bain & Company, a global business consulting firm where he was a senior executive in its Global Healthcare Practice Group and a leading client service partner.  Prior to his work at Bain, Elgar spent more than a decade at McKinsey and Company in various leadership roles. Throughout his career, Elgar has focused on serving customers across the global healthcare industry, including many pharmaceutical and biotech companies. He has extensive leadership experience in strategy, business definition and models, research, clinical development, go-to-market strategies and post-merger integration.



